    37	- 2026-04-26 [schema][defer-blocks-without-commander-backing] **Don't scaffold-lock blocks that have no current Commander surface; defer to v1.1.** P14 worker's BLOCK MIGRATION TABLE flagged `service_mappings` and `saas_mappings` as having no defined Commander command currently backing them — listing them as proposed top-level keys in V2_DECISIONS.md was aspirational, not evidence-backed. Worker's recommendation: defer both to a v1.1 follow-up rather than scaffold-locking placeholder shapes. This is the schema-family analogue of P13b's dropped-design pattern: better to have N-2 blocks shipping cleanly than N blocks where 2 are ghost-scaffolds. Pattern: every proposed top-level block in V2 table must cite a Commander source path (file:line) at memo-time; if memo can't find one, the block defers, not ships.
